com.kuka.med.jogging

Interface IJoggingService


  • public interface IJoggingService
    Capability interface for jogging a serial kinematic (robot) from a robotics application.

    • Method Detail

      • startJointJogging

        boolean startJointJogging(Set<com.kuka.device.common.JointEnum> joints,
                          double velocity,
                          long joggingTimeInMilliseconds)
        Starts a joint jogging motion for all specified joints with the specified velocity, which applies to all joints. The jogging motion is active for the specified jogging time, unless the value -1 is set to indicate an infinite jogging motion. This is only allowed, if no other motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        joints - joints to be jogged.
        velocity - Velocity override must be between -1.0 and 1.0.
        joggingTimeInMilliseconds - Jogging time in milliseconds [ms].
        Returns:
        True, if joint Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

      • startJointJogging

        boolean startJointJogging(Map<com.kuka.device.common.JointEnum,Double> joints,
                          long joggingTimeInMilliseconds)
        Starts a joint jogging motion for all specified joints with the specified velocity for each joint. The jogging motion is active for the specified jogging time, unless the value -1 is set to indicate an infinite jogging motion. This is only allowed, if no other motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        joints - Map of joint to be jogged and a corresponding velocity override, which must be between -1.0 and 1.0
        joggingTimeInMilliseconds - Jogging time in milliseconds [ms].
        Returns:
        True, if joint Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

      • startJointJogging

        boolean startJointJogging(Set<com.kuka.device.common.JointEnum> joints,
                          double velocity)
        Starts a joint jogging motion for all specified joints with the specified velocity, which applies to all joints. The default timeout condition (5sec) is enabled. This is only allowed, if no other motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        joints - joints to be jogged.
        velocity - Velocity override must be between -1.0 and 1.0.
        Returns:
        True, if joint Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

      • startCartesianJogging

        boolean startCartesianJogging(Set<com.kuka.roboticsAPI.deviceModel.CartesianCoordinates> coordinates,
                              double velocity,
                              com.kuka.roboticsAPI.motionModel.CartesianJoggingMode cartJoggingMode,
                              long joggingTimeInMilliseconds)
        Starts a Cartesian jogging motion for all specified DoF with the specified velocity and mode. The jogging motion is active for the specified jogging time, unless the value -1 is set to indicate an infinite jogging motion. The default base frame is identical to the world. The default tcp frame is identical to the default motion frame of the robot. This is only allowed, if no jogging motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        coordinates - DoF of the Cartesian motion.
        velocity - Velocity must be between -1.0 and 1.0.
        cartJoggingMode - Jogging modality of the Cartesian Motion.
        joggingTimeInMilliseconds - Jogging time in milliseconds [ms]
        Returns:
        True, if Cartesian Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a joint jogging motion is already active.

      • startCartesianJogging

        boolean startCartesianJogging(Map<com.kuka.roboticsAPI.deviceModel.CartesianCoordinates,Double> coordinates,
                              com.kuka.roboticsAPI.motionModel.CartesianJoggingMode cartJoggingMode,
                              long joggingTimeInMilliseconds)
        Starts a Cartesian jogging motion for all specified DoF with the specified velocity for each DoF and mode. The jogging motion is active for the specified jogging time, unless the value -1 is set to indicate an infinite jogging motion. The default base frame is identical to the world. The default tcp frame is identical to the default motion frame of the robot. This is only allowed, if no jogging motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        coordinates - Map of Cartesian DoFs to be jogged and a corresponding velocity override, which must be between -1.0 and 1.0
        cartJoggingMode - Jogging modality of the Cartesian Motion.
        joggingTimeInMilliseconds - Jogging time in milliseconds [ms]
        Returns:
        True, if Cartesian Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a joint jogging motion is already active.

      • startCartesianJogging

        boolean startCartesianJogging(Set<com.kuka.roboticsAPI.deviceModel.CartesianCoordinates> coordinates,
                              double velocity,
                              com.kuka.roboticsAPI.motionModel.CartesianJoggingMode cartJoggingMode)
        Starts a Cartesian jogging motion for all specified DoF with the specified velocity and mode. The default base frame is identical to the world. The default tcp frame is identical to the default motion frame of the robot. The default timeout condition (5sec) is enabled. This is only allowed, if no jogging motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        coordinates - DoF of the Cartesian motion.
        velocity - Velocity must be between -1.0 and 1.0
        cartJoggingMode - Jogging modality of the Cartesian Motion.
        Returns:
        True, if Cartesian Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a joint jogging motion is already active.

                              com.kuka.roboticsAPI.motionModel.CartesianJoggingMode cartJoggingMode)
        Starts a Cartesian jogging motion for all specified DoF with a specified velocity for each DoF and mode. The default base frame is identical to the world. The default tcp frame is identical to the default motion frame of the robot. The default timeout condition (5sec) is enabled. This is only allowed, if no jogging motion is already running.
        Parameters:
        coordinates - Map of Cartesian DoFs to be jogged and a corresponding velocity override, which must be between -1.0 and 1.0
        cartJoggingMode - Jogging modality of the Cartesian Motion.
        Returns:
        True, if Cartesian Jogging motion is started.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If one the arguments is invalid.
        IllegalStateException - If a joint jogging motion is already active.

        joints - joints of the joint motion to be stopped.

        True, if the joint jogging motion was active and was correctly stopped.

      • isJoggingActive

        boolean isJoggingActive()
        Indicates whether jogging is currently active or not.
        Returns:
        True, if joint or Cartesian jogging is currently active, false otherwise.

      • setTcp

        void setTcp(com.kuka.geometry.ObjectFrame tcp)
        Sets the TCP for Cartesian motions. If the frame is null the default motion frame of the robot is used.

        The frame must be attached to the robot, otherwise a IllegalStateException will be thrown.

        Parameters:
        tcp - ObjectFrame for Cartesian motions.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

      • setBase

        void setBase(com.kuka.geometry.ObjectFrame base)
        Sets the BASE for Cartesian motions. If the frame is null the world frame is used.
        Parameters:
        base - ObjectFrame for Cartesian motions.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If a Cartesian jogging motion is already active.

      • stopJoggingAtJointLimitOrSingularity

        void stopJoggingAtJointLimitOrSingularity(boolean activeForJointJogging,
                                          boolean activeForCartesianJogging)
        Activate or deactivate the noMotion stop condition, i.e. the jogging command will be stopped if the robot does not move due to joint limits or singularity poses. The default status of the noMotion stop condition is ACTIVE. The method must be called while no jogging motion is active, otherwise an IllegalStateException will be thrown.
        Parameters:
        activeForJointJogging - True, if condition is activated for joint jogging commands.
        activeForCartesianJogging - True, if condition is activated for Cartesian jogging commands.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If a jogging motion is already active.

      • getFiredStopCondition

        EJoggingStopCondition getFiredStopCondition()
        Gets the last fired stop condition for the jogging motion. If the jogging motion is active, NONE type will be returned. If a jogging motion was never started, the type JOGGING_NEVER_STARTED is returned.
        Returns:
        The fired stop condition for the jogging motion.
